beautiful, interactive material.

00:16:40.500 --> 00:16:43.700
This is an example of what not to do.

00:16:44.350 --> 00:16:48.250
As I mentioned before,
about 8% of the male population

00:16:48.290 --> 00:16:50.580
has a form of color blindness.

00:16:50.970 --> 00:16:53.680
Those of you who may be familiar
with it may know that red and

00:16:53.680 --> 00:16:55.280
green is the most common form.

00:16:55.350 --> 00:16:59.800
The ability to differentiate between
blue and orange is also one of the types.

00:16:59.800 --> 00:17:04.290
And so this information is
presented only with color.

00:17:04.350 --> 00:17:07.300
So the key thing to remember
here is not which colors you use,

00:17:07.330 --> 00:17:10.300
but don't present
information with color alone.

00:17:10.300 --> 00:17:14.950
So this is how it may look to someone
with a particular vision impairment.

00:17:15.620 --> 00:17:18.460
And there's a lot of ways,
I mean obviously this is ridiculous,

00:17:18.460 --> 00:17:18.880
right?

00:17:18.960 --> 00:17:21.150
Doesn't make any sense at all.

00:17:21.280 --> 00:17:23.520
But there's a lot of ways that we
can retrofit this and some of it is

00:17:23.590 --> 00:17:27.140
the way you design the chart and some
of it is maybe a little bit in the

00:17:27.150 --> 00:17:30.000
colors that you choose based on value.

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:32.680
For example, we could make a darker blue,
for example,

00:17:32.750 --> 00:17:36.490
so even though the orange was there,
it was lighter.

00:17:37.580 --> 00:17:39.740
But that's not going
to work for all users.

00:17:39.740 --> 00:17:44.530
And so the critical bit that we added
to this retrofit was that we added the

00:17:44.540 --> 00:17:47.300
percentages to the key here as well.

00:17:47.470 --> 00:17:49.580
Now, this is a design afterthought.

00:17:49.700 --> 00:17:52.490
There's a lot of ways that we could
redo this to make it even better.

00:17:52.660 --> 00:17:56.760
But the critical bit here is that even
if you took away the rest of that chart,

00:17:57.490 --> 00:18:02.350
The user can still see the point
of the information from this.

00:18:02.350 --> 00:18:05.070
Now, to give you a better example of

00:18:05.300 --> 00:18:24.100
[Transcript missing]

00:18:24.370 --> 00:18:26.970
and the designers used red and green.

00:18:26.970 --> 00:18:30.990
It's the most common form of
color blindness that prevents some

00:18:30.990 --> 00:18:33.320
users from seeing red and green.

00:18:33.440 --> 00:18:35.000
It's okay to use color.

00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:36.740
Color is inherent in our culture.

00:18:36.740 --> 00:18:38.340
It means stop and go.

00:18:38.340 --> 00:18:39.200
It means right and wrong.

00:18:39.200 --> 00:18:42.560
