00:36:08.660 --> 00:36:12.100
And each one of these
things represents a button.

00:36:12.170 --> 00:36:15.640
But as Jason will show you in the code,
it was just a meaningless,

00:36:15.800 --> 00:36:19.100
semantically meaningless div
with a class affront on it.

00:36:19.120 --> 00:36:21.100
And so we're actually going to
add role equals button to that.

00:36:21.100 --> 00:36:25.290
And this will tell WebKit, rather,
to send that information to

00:36:25.290 --> 00:36:28.240
the accessibility API and
VoiceOver can read that and

00:36:28.320 --> 00:36:30.370
understand that this is a button.

00:36:31.220 --> 00:36:35.200
Likewise, on the back side of this,
we have these dialogues,

00:36:35.270 --> 00:36:37.640
but they're just another div,
and it's got more content in it,

00:36:37.640 --> 00:36:42.090
but we want to associate this with
the type of application dialogue.

00:36:42.150 --> 00:36:44.250
Now,
there is no HTML attribute for dialogue.

00:36:44.300 --> 00:36:48.600
There used to be one that was about
dialogue or discussion between people,

00:36:48.600 --> 00:36:50.100
but I don't even think
