00:36:50.100 --> 00:36:53.850
We're talking about
application dialogues.

00:36:53.940 --> 00:36:57.210
So the next thing you want to do is
update your states and properties.

00:36:58.480 --> 00:37:00.160
So in addition to the fact
that this is a button,

00:37:00.160 --> 00:37:03.550
we also want to give it
a label such as the moon.

00:37:03.550 --> 00:37:06.160
And remember, at this point,
the dialogue that's on the

00:37:06.170 --> 00:37:08.800
backside is actually hidden
from view to the sighted user.

00:37:08.800 --> 00:37:11.350
And so we want to make sure that
VoiceOver knows that as well.

00:37:11.410 --> 00:37:14.630
So we're going to say this
dialogue or these dialogues that

00:37:14.680 --> 00:37:18.300
are out of view now are hidden
via this ARIA hidden attribute.

00:37:19.000 --> 00:37:22.580
Now when we show that dialogue,
we have to update the state.

00:37:22.720 --> 00:37:26.340
And so we're going to dynamically
change that hidden state to false,

00:37:26.340 --> 00:37:27.700
making it shown.

00:37:27.820 --> 00:37:31.300
It's already in view because
we showed it with some CSS,

00:37:31.300 --> 00:37:35.530
but we're also going to make sure
that VoiceOver can see this now too.

00:37:36.430 --> 00:37:39.090
and likewise the buttons that are
on the front are now hidden from

00:37:39.090 --> 00:37:42.540
view so we want to make sure that
VoiceOver knows that those shouldn't

00:37:42.540 --> 00:37:44.060
be accessible at this point.

00:37:44.180 --> 00:37:48.360
So we're going to set those to be hidden.

00:37:48.470 --> 00:37:51.780
The last bit of the chain is
that you want to manage focus.

00:37:52.830 --> 00:37:57.690
Now when we have this button
on the front and we tap,

00:37:57.830 --> 00:37:59.940
there's an animation that occurs
and so a side user can see,

