00:38:34.980 --> 00:38:38.060
The next thing that I want you
to know about ARIA is it's really

00:38:38.060 --> 00:38:40.130
good at retrofitting old content.

00:38:40.270 --> 00:38:43.400
So for that class up front,
we could have re-architected

00:38:43.400 --> 00:38:43.960
the application.

00:38:43.960 --> 00:38:47.660
We could have changed this to
use a button element in HTML.

00:38:47.750 --> 00:38:48.460
But we don't have to.

00:38:48.460 --> 00:38:49.940
ARIA allows us to go back in.

00:38:50.330 --> 00:38:53.660
You may have inherited code before
that didn't have certain features.

00:38:53.660 --> 00:38:56.310
And so it allows you to easily go
back in and change things so you

00:38:56.390 --> 00:38:59.350
don't have to gut your application.

00:38:59.440 --> 00:39:03.890
You can also set these properties
using the DOMSetAttribute method.

00:39:05.490 --> 00:39:08.580
A lot of people ask me,
how do I know when I'm supposed

00:39:08.580 --> 00:39:10.360
to update these ARIA properties?

00:39:10.360 --> 00:39:14.160
How do I know when I add one of
these attributes or remove or

00:39:14.220 --> 00:39:16.340
change one of these attributes?

00:39:16.710 --> 00:39:20.060
A good indication is if
you're changing element style.

00:39:20.060 --> 00:39:23.110
In this case,
if you change a class name to something

00:39:23.140 --> 00:39:26.920
like hidden or if you change a style,
especially if it's something like a

00:39:26.960 --> 00:39:34.400
meaningful class name like highlight or
active or focused or selected or hidden,

00:39:34.480 --> 00:39:38.000
that's usually a good indication that you
want to update an ARIA attribute as well.

00:39:38.020 --> 00:39:42.180
And so in this case,
we're going to update the

00:39:42.180 --> 00:39:45.340
ARIA hidden attribute to true.

00:39:45.410 --> 00:39:47.830
Now, I mentioned managing focus.

00:39:48.930 --> 00:39:52.610
The key thing to keep in mind is
that VoiceOver cursor focus is

00:39:52.610 --> 00:39:54.240
not the same as keyboard focus.

00:39:54.360 --> 00:39:58.870
iOS doesn't really have this concept
of keyboard focus except in a couple

00:39:58.940 --> 00:40:01.300
places where you can type in text.

00:40:01.410 --> 00:40:04.530
And so when I'm talking about
managing focus here on iOS and iBooks,

00:40:04.590 --> 00:40:07.740
I'm talking about just moving
the VoiceOver cursor around.

