00:50:55.220 --> 00:50:57.190
So let's review what we've learned.

00:50:57.350 --> 00:50:59.900
Standard HTML accessibility
techniques still apply.

00:51:00.020 --> 00:51:03.310
You can still label your images with the
alt text if you need to label something

00:51:03.880 --> 00:51:09.200
that represents an image or a button or
something that's not natively in HTML.

00:51:09.200 --> 00:51:12.630
You can add the aria-label attribute.

00:51:14.560 --> 00:51:19.710
And like I said, HTML only goes so far,
so there is no dialogue element.

00:51:19.710 --> 00:51:22.490
There is no -- well, until recently,
there was no slider element.

00:51:22.580 --> 00:51:25.880
So there's a lot of places where
ARIA can update the semantics of

00:51:25.930 --> 00:51:28.960
your application where HTML cannot.

00:51:29.350 --> 00:51:30.370
You want to manage focus.

00:51:30.400 --> 00:51:32.010
So any time your
application state changes,

00:51:32.010 --> 00:51:34.750
as it did when we flipped from
the front of those buttons to

00:51:34.760 --> 00:51:38.340
the back of one of the dialogs,
you want to move focus in

00:51:38.340 --> 00:51:42.120
so that VoiceOver knows that
that event has occurred too.

00:51:43.270 --> 00:51:47.540
and test, test,
test your books with VoiceOver.

00:51:47.540 --> 00:51:52.580
So that's an overview of
accessibility in iBooks.

00:51:52.580 --> 00:51:55.870
Some of the takeaways that
I want you to walk away with

00:51:56.050 --> 00:51:58.120
are that books are for everyone.

00:51:58.120 --> 00:52:01.680
Education is a great equalizer and
that benefit of education through

00:52:01.760 --> 00:52:06.670
books should be available to all people
including those with disabilities.

00:52:08.920 --> 00:52:11.740
Likewise, accessibility is for everyone.

00:52:11.740 --> 00:52:14.810
Sometimes it has the stigma of
it's just for a small group of

00:52:14.900 --> 00:52:16.860
people so I shouldn't be doing this.

00:52:16.860 --> 00:52:20.040
As you saw in the example
of closed captions,

00:52:20.040 --> 00:52:24.500
there can be a lot of benefit
besides the necessity that is

00:52:24.560 --> 00:52:26.720
needed for people with disabilities.

00:52:26.810 --> 00:52:31.630
Accessibility is for everyone including
those with disabilities but not

00:52:31.710 --> 00:52:34.360
limited to those with disabilities.

00:52:34.980 --> 00:52:37.260
And adding accessibility
to books is really easy.

00:52:37.380 --> 00:52:39.560
For the most part,
we were just adding alternative text.

00:52:39.570 --> 00:52:42.460
